Text: Why're ye wastin' words on the poor sod ye bested? Ye know yer path, an' there ain't naught to stop ye from walkin' it.
Forgemaster H'naanza was my inspiration for joining the guild, and I believe I've made some small progress in attaining her skill with hammer and pliers.

But when I see how swiftly you've learned─and mastered─the techniques of armorcraft, my accomplishments seem paltry indeed by comparison. I know not what more of my spirit I can surrender to this art...
<split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>! How fare your efforts at the forge? I trust your growing fame hasn't convinced you to neglect your skills?
We all need the abundant inspiration your impeccable armorcraft provides! Speaking of which, I must needs return to my latest creation─just as soon as I find my pliers...
I've been rather more careful with the size of the commissions I accept these days. The forgemaster has been forgiving of my past mistakes, but I cannot remain a coddled novice forever.
Ever since Guildmaster Fufucha returned to the Growery, we've all observed a certain spring in her step.
Has she found a new love, or merely rekindled an old one? This I cannot say, but we are all heartened to see her well.
The nerve of some outsiders, waltzing into Gridania as if they were the elementals' gift to the Twelveswood... I'll wager most of them don't even know what a hoe is!
...But not you, my friend, oh no. As you have proven to us all, you are a womanman who knows herhis hoes.
Mind the flowerpots! You break it, you bought it!
...And yes, that goes for you as well! If you think being Fufucha's favorite will earn you special treatment, you are gravely mistaken.
If I have served in my own humble way to restore Fufucha's faith in her profession, it is the very least I could have done after all that she has imparted to me.
Verily, there is much I would still learn from my mentor. I can but hope she will grace these bleak highlands with her presence once more.
When I was first made the guild's registrar, I was grateful for the chance to be out of the scorching sun and the choking dust.
But your adventures have gotten me itching to get my hands dirty again. The only problem is, I haven't done any digging for so long, I'm not sure I can even lift a sledgehammer anymore...
You may have double mooched a Mazlaya marlin, but don't dismiss the remaining denizens of the deep!
If you truly fancy yourself a formidable fisher, you'd best set about bringing in the biggest fish you can bag!
You needn't nab the Nepto Dragon next, you know. Plenty of phenomenal prizes have yet to be plucked from Eorzea's waters.
Therein lies another lesson for both love and our labor: let not the pursuit of perfection blind you to the next best thing!
Well, well! Catching a Mazlaya marlin is no mean feat! Even the guildmaster would be hard-pressed to reel in such a beast.
I wonder─ Did he see your prodigious potential from the start, or did he endorse your enrollment on a lark?
Chuchuroon want to taste fish fished by <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)> again! The smelly smell, the tasty taste!
Chuchuroon try to fish fish for Chuchuroon with fake fish food, but fish no fool. No hope for hopeless Chuchuroon...
Raya–O might be more affable than her brother, but she's not one to spout words of idle flattery.
...This I speak from experience. Yes, you've proven yourself a worthy white mage indeed, kupo!
Why, I'd give my pom and tail to stand before the illustrious A–Towa–Cant!
And yet now I stand before you─which as I've heard from Raya–O is the next best thing, kupo!
On most days, the sylphs are a harmless enough bunch, but with the state of the realm of late, one can never exercise too much caution.
I hear that denizens of Little Solace have taken a liking to you. Any further news you could glean from your fluttery friends would be most appreciated.

Well, if it isn't <If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(52),0))><split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)><Else/><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(53),0))><Head><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(52),0))><sheet(GCRankLimsaMaleText,PlayerParameter(52),8)><Else/> </If><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(53),0))><sheet(GCRankGridaniaMaleText,PlayerParameter(53),8)><Else/> </If><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(54),0))><sheet(GCRankUldahMaleText,PlayerParameter(54),8)><Else/> </If></Head> <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,2)><Else/><split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)></If></If>, slayer of  “Great” King Moggle Mog XII─may he... \\<cough> Ahem.

On behalf of our entire nation, I thank you for your heroic efforts. <If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(52),0))>Gridania is indebted to you for your aid.<Else/><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(53),0))>You are a model to your fellow Serpents.<Else/>Gridania is indebted to you for your aid.</If></If>

Oft have we resorted to force to resolve our disputes with the beastmen, but not without heavy hearts. Voyce's exploits in Little Solace─in which you played an ample role, or so I hear─are welcome proof that peace is yet within our reach.

For returning a measure of quietude to the Twelveswood, the elementals surely smile upon us. You have my thanks, <If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(52),0))><split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)><Else/><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(53),0))><Head><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(52),0))><sheet(GCRankLimsaMaleText,PlayerParameter(52),8)><Else/> </If><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(53),0))><sheet(GCRankGridaniaMaleText,PlayerParameter(53),8)><Else/> </If><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(54),0))><sheet(GCRankUldahMaleText,PlayerParameter(54),8)><Else/> </If></Head> <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,2)><Else/><split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)></If></If>.
The list of victims falling prey to Amalj'aa thrall-takers grows longer by the day. Our forces in southern Thanalan are stretched thin, and your help is sorely needed.

<If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(52),0))><split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)><Else/><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(53),0))><split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)><Else/><Head><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(52),0))><sheet(GCRankLimsaMaleText,PlayerParameter(52),8)><Else/> </If><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(53),0))><sheet(GCRankGridaniaMaleText,PlayerParameter(53),8)><Else/> </If><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(54),0))><sheet(GCRankUldahMaleText,PlayerParameter(54),8)><Else/> </If></Head> <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,2)></If></If>, I must thank you once again for avenging my fallen scouts.
Ifrit has ever been an untamable force of destruction, and I feared that the primal's latest incarnation was an inferno beyond anyone's ability to quench. Ul'dah is in your debt.
Your actions in southern Thanalan have done much to restore peace to the region.
Though I would be foolish to think the Amalj'aa cowed for good, this respite gives us the chance to recoup our strength. I will be sure to call upon you again should the need arise.

If we cannot ensure the safety of merchants at sea, then trade in Limsa Lominsa will grind to a halt. We must bolster our forces in western La Noscea, and take the fight to the fishbacks. Can I count on your cooperation?

<If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(52),0))><Head><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(52),0))><sheet(GCRankLimsaMaleText,PlayerParameter(52),8)><Else/> </If><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(53),0))><sheet(GCRankGridaniaMaleText,PlayerParameter(53),8)><Else/> </If><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(54),0))><sheet(GCRankUldahMaleText,PlayerParameter(54),8)><Else/> </If></Head> <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,2)><Else/><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(53),0))><split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)><Else/><split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)></If></If>! I have heard word of your victory over that calamitous sea snake!

Truly, the power manifested by Leviathan was unheard of. Had you failed, Limsa Lominsa─nay, all of La Noscea─would now be drowning under a hundred yalms of water. <If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(52),0))>You are the pride of the Maelstrom<Else/><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(53),0))>You are a true hero<Else/>You are a true hero</If></If>!
As long as the Sahagin threaten Limsa Lominsa, the Maelstrom stands ready to throw them back into the sea.
But your successes at Halfstone have proven that not all battles need be fought with a blade. Mayhap there is hope that a peaceful resolution to this conflict can be found.
So we've rodents to thank for our stray shipment of saltpeter─and a real piss-poor pack of them, at that?
I almost pity the furry buggers when I think of what awaits them at Skaetswys's 'ands. She's not one to suffer fools lightly...

Ah, <If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(52),0))><Head><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(52),0))><sheet(GCRankLimsaMaleText,PlayerParameter(52),8)><Else/> </If><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(53),0))><sheet(GCRankGridaniaMaleText,PlayerParameter(53),8)><Else/> </If><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(54),0))><sheet(GCRankUldahMaleText,PlayerParameter(54),8)><Else/> </If></Head> <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,2)><Else/><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(53),0))><split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)><Else/><split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)></If></If>. Ye've done the Maelstrom proud.
Peace with the kobolds won't come easily, but yer efforts have given us something to build on.
That said, could ye not have befriended a more inspirin' lot?

Your valorous deeds are well known among our soldiers, my friend. Indeed, so many of our recruits are striving to become the next <String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, 'tis all I can do to tell them not to overreach.
The boy gave ye no choice, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. Ye just did what ye had to do. Ain't a Wailer here who'd say otherwise.
I'm sorry I involved you in my affairs, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. If I hadn't, perhaps Ailbert would not have... \\<sigh>

Have I mentioned that Leia's egg has hatched? We have yet to settle on a name, but the chick is healthy, spirited, and incurably inquisitive. She will receive the finest care, and shall one day grow into an exceptional chocobo.

Oh, aren't you the adventurer who was Emissary at Greenbliss? To be chosen for the role is a great honor, and doubly so if you're not forestborn. The Elder Seedseer doubtless sees great things in you.
How goes it, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>? Keeping your equipment in good condition? One should never forget the fundamentals!
You've taken a liking to our lovely little hamlet, haven't you? Or mayhap to the lovely little Kikipu?
Oh, don't give me that look! A lady must indulge in pretension from time to time!
I know full well that Baldewyn's arrest was but the first step towards regaining the public trust. As acting captain, I will continue to do my utmost to repair the Brass Blades' reputation!
During the course of my official tenure as a Sultansworn, I traveled the length and breadth of Eorzea. Those experiences molded me into the man I am today.
You have been blessed with the skills and opportunities to do the same, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. I pray you do not squander them.
I would thank you again for rescuing the Victory from an explosive end, but mere words could never fully express my gratitude.

The pirates' attempt at sabotaging the hope of Limsa Lominsa may have failed, but they did succeed in exposing the chinks in the armor of our vigilance. If we are to prevent any such incident from happening again, we cannot allow our lack of resources to serve as an excuse for negligence.

I expect great things from you, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. After all, 'twould be remiss of me as commodore to heap praise upon an adventurer who did naught but rest on <If(PlayerParameter(4))>her<Else/>his</If> laurels!
And I am certain there are many others within La Noscea who share my confidence in your continued success.
With the false priest apprehended, the people of Camp Drybone may go about their lives with easier hearts. You have my gratitude, friend.
This one has not met such a kind walking one in many moons. Walking one will return, yes? Return, and make merry with these ones!
Noraxia is no longer with these ones, but this one does not weep. Noraxia has returned to the forest whence all ones are born.
For every end, there is a beginning, and the cycle begins anew. Walking one will forever have this one's gratitude for bringing Noraxia home.
Walking one has proven a true friend to these ones. From the first time walking one arrived in Little Solace, this one believed this day would come.
Listen to the murmurs of the forest, walking one. Noraxia, too, is proud to call walking one friend.
Friendly one walks like walking one, but friendly one's heart is one with these ones. Friendly one will forever have a home in Little Solace.
Chosen One, Noraxia, this one─all ones watch over friendly one, that peace and happiness will follow wherever friendly one goes.
Always a pleasure, my friend. No doubt you're weary from the road. Sit yourself down wherever you like.
The Qiqirn firewater still wants for aging, but we've got no shortage of other quality brews.
Seems you've been keeping busy of late, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>lass<Else/>lad</If>. What's all this talk I hear about you becoming some great hero, eh?
Well, whenever the weight of fame gets too heavy, you just bend your course hither. Whatever you might be outside, at the Druthers you're free to be just another soul seeking a moment of respite.
Well, if it isn't <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>! I hear tell that you and the Scions've relocated to Mor Dhona.
It's a long way from here, to be sure. Which gladdens me all the more that you've made time to pay old Buscarron visit.
<split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>, what a pleasant surprise! I heard they opened up a tavern at Revenant's Toll, and I was afraid you wouldn't come here any more.
But of course, I needn't have worried. It ain't only the grog what brings people to the Druthers, but the camaraderie. And that is something we've got in abundance.
Our brother Gallien yet lives thanks to you. As unwanted refugees in this land, we have little and less to offer by way of gratitude, but one day, I swear to repay your kindness thrice over.
How fare your travels, adventurer? Though it barely begins to repay the debt you are owed, you will always find a safe haven here.
And you need not be concerned with young Wilred. The pain and regret he feels is a common burden amongst Ala Mhigans, and one we willingly bear─it reminds us to always strive for a better life.
<split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. I hear word that you've been seen in the company of Amalj'aa. And yet your actions against their kinsmen are not those of a tempered thrall.

I know not what bonds you have forged, but I have seen how barriers of race and position mean little to one such as you. After all, you did not let our cold Ala Mhigan walls prevent you from saving us from our own folly.
Seems to me the Amalj'aa have been unusually quiet of late. I wonder who we have to thank for that small miracle, hmmm?
Though the effects of your actions may not be immediately apparent, rest assured that they are felt─and appreciated─long after you have moved on.

They call me a workin' man, I reckon that's what I am.♪
I work with me head, so others get tired instead.♪
At least until the word spreads.♪

They call me a workin' man, I reckon that's what I am.♪
Drinkin' under the chief's nose, sneakin' out the back door.♪
Aaand nobody'll ever know.♪
If I weren't bound by me duties here, I'd be out there crackin' imperial skulls right about now. Ah, the price of bein' an honorable soul!

They call me a workin' man, I reckon that's what I am.♪
Makin' friends with heroes, helpin' them to best their foes.♪
Aaand nobody'll ever know.♪
We are all praying for your success, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. Now, go and send that bastard back to the depths from which he came.
You have earned your title, Titan's Bane.
I pray it did not come at too great a cost.
Come to think of it, I never did ask what sort of trouble she had gotten herself into. Now that it's been settled, mind telling me what it was?
...Cheese? Again!? I should have never asked.

...Not that it's any of my business, but the next time a nation is in danger of imminent destruction at the hands of a primal, you might consider consulting those who have fought and felled it before.
In any case, I am glad to see you alive and well.
You've nothing left to prove, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. Nor do you require further assistance from me. You know what you must do next.
Word travels fast in the Company. Ground him beneath your heel, did you? Hah! A bloody harpymagnificent bastard after my own heart.
You are a skilled hunterrr, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. This I know. But your quarry is a god; this I also know.
Blind rrrecklessness will avail you naught against such foes, regardless of what Landenel may claim.
Although your victory over Titan was a foregone conclusion in mine eyes, I am nevertheless rrrelieved to see you healthy and hale.
Know that you will always be welcome in Forgotten Springs, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. The U do not forrrget their friends.

Pshhh... Shkohhh...
Goodly uplander is talentful plansmaker! Will trade tongueflaps with Wheiskaet so all know of hand-lending!

Pshhh... Shkohhh...
Mighty rockman no match for wily uplander and clever fighty-think! Brayflox happytoasts fall of rockman!

Pshhh... Shkohhh...
Cheese is gobbie birthright! Gobbietreat for every gobbieflock! If Illuminati deephate Brayflox, then Brayflox backhate Illuminati!
To think that Drest would chance upon the key to reviving the Bacchus vineyards!
I owe you many thanks as well, my friend, for you are the one who has set these events in motion.
\\<sniff> \\<sniff> The scent of the Navel clings to you still.
...Did you truly think me that perceptive? No, no─I learned of your victory from Captain Wheiskaet. I raised a glass in your honor that very eve.
\\<sniff> \\<sniff> I see you managed to find the perfumed lady. And...a goobbue? Oh dear.
She is well? Thank the Twelve! For a moment, I was concerned you had arrived too late.
I heard a most interesting rumor the other day. Apparently, Castrum Occidens was built primarily as a research facility, as the Garleans had taken an interest in certain subterranean caverns.
Moreover, a certain adventurer was said to have infiltrated the castrum and located the entrance to the caverns in question! Fascinating, wouldn't you agree?
...Of course I know it was you. My ears are almost as sharp as my nose, in case you were unaware.
You and Cid shall ever be in my thoughts, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. Return whenever you require respite.
Have you perchance come here in search of Cid? If so, I fear I must disappoint you. Though he paid me a visit, it was regrettably brief, for he had more pressing matters to attend to in Mor Dhona.
Hildibrand? Why, yes, there is a gentleman interred here by that name. If you have come to pay your respects, I can─
He has risen!? Thal forgive me, I thought we had rid the lichyard of zombies...
Minfilia has been blessed with a rare opportunity. Most have no choice but to await passage into Thal's realm to reunite with the lost.
Your service to House Fortemps will not be forgotten, my friend. If ever you have need of me, do not hesitate to ask.
House Haillenarte is far from redeemed, but one day we will regain our standing. When that day comes, rest assured I will repay my debts to you and Lord Haurchefant.
I trust you will not discuss the events which transpired at Snowcloak too openly.
The heretic is dead, and the lords of the High Houses know of your deeds. That is what matters.
Now that you've driven off that pesky siren and slain her undead thralls, I suppose I can visit the Isles of Umbra for my research.
On the other hand, it can be rather difficult to determine if the undead are sufficiently...dead.
I must say, I'm impressed that you all managed to repair that suit of armor. I've a mind to go out and acquire my own now.
For obvious reasons, Castrum Centri has been quiet of late. I don't expect it will last, but for now we can focus on fortifying the Toll.
The Toll owes much to the generous contributions of the Elder Seedseer and the Antecedent.
Heh heh, I know you were involved too, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. Gave the Mogglesguard and their king what for, eh? Well done.
Hah! First the Elder Seedseer favors us with provisions, and now the Admiral sees fit to do the same.
She couldn't have chosen a more opportune time. These days, between the Domans and the adventurers, the Toll feels less an outpost and more an honest-to-gods city!
To survive in this uncertain world, a man's gotta know both his talents an' his limits. I've done my part in the fight─the rest is up to you an' yours, my friend.
With the Black Wolf slain an' his pack scattered, Revenant's Toll's begun to take on new life. As for me, I daresay I'm beginnin' to see a future worth livin' for─a future not ruled by vengeance.
Ah, Titan's Bane! That is your title, yes? Pray partake of Costa del Sol's hospitality.
However, do try to refrain from crude displays of martial prowess. This is a place of beauty and leisure─not the bloodsands.
Why have you not yet returned to me, my beloved F'lhaminn!? What malevolent forces conspire to keep us apart!?
...A daughter, you say? Hmmm... If she bears even the slightest resemblance to her mother, I should like very much to meet her.
Teteroon miss good Buscaroon. Must work hard. Must make many shinies. Then Teteroon go see Buscaroon!
Another day, another hundred pilgrims not coming to Highbridge and parting with their coin as they should. \\ But enough about my quandaries.

Oh, have you chanced to meet my daughter at Little Ala Mhigo? She's ever been a dreamer, my Hihira, and headstrong besides. I've long given up on having her obey me─it's enough to know that she's alive and well.
Graaaaaah! The sun, it still burns! Will my poor pate never know relief!? What other adorable critter's blood must I drench it with before my suffering is ended!?
Yer a bloody fool to be standin' here, but a bloody strong fool to do so without gettin' yerself killed.
Ye'll find no respite on the front lines. If ye've a mind to stick around, I'll be trustin' ye to make yerself useful.
Hush, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>woman<Else/>man</If>. I cannot focus on the flow of aether when your breathing is so loud!
If you intend to remain in my presence, I must insist that you hold your breath.

The professor's thesis also postulates the existence of corrupted crystals which could be likened to specialized converters, in that they could only be used to alter aether of a single aspect to aether of another aspect─say, earth to fire, for instance.
Yet my research thus far suggests that such crystals do not exist. Could it be that the professor is─dare I say it─wrong?
Again you disrupt my research─and for what!? You have your crystal. What more do you need?
Whatever it is, I do not care. I, Hahasako, greatest of Professor Lamberteint's pupils, can suffer no further distractions! Away with you!
Would that we could recognize your deeds more openly, but you know well our circumstance. That may change in future, but the present demands discretion.

We may have crushed the ambitions of the Serpent Reavers, but their fishback masters yet threaten our shores. Let them come, I say. No Sahagin force shall breach the tidegates─not while I remain in command!
So dutifully did I serve my lady in happier times, only to forsake her when she needed me most.
My failures will forever haunt me. And yet with your brave deeds, mayhap my lady's tormented soul will find peace after so many years of woe.

I presume the brave adventurer the Wood Wailer captain spoke of was you. I was in a state of astonishment at the time─to think that someone could enter the manor not merely once, but twice, and return to tell the tale.
Oh, my lady... My poor, tormented lady... Will her soul know no reprieve from the clutches of darkness?
My shame, my dishonor for my role in the fall of the Dartancours─these I must bear unto my grave. My only hope is that you have brought an end to these years of tragedy and woe.
'Tis my most fervent belief that the fellowship of NOAH will─piece by piece─lay bare the long-buried secrets of ancient Allag's history. But the doing of it will require all of your skill and more!
Mayhap I can convince Master Garlond to allow me to accompany you, that I might see some of these horrific guardians in the flesh. I am quite proficient with the bow, you know!

Though I don't doubt your abilities, none can say what dangers lurk beneath Castrum Occidens. For my lady's sake as well as your own, please spare neither preparation nor caution. Pray choose your companions well.

I understand you navigated your way to the deepest sector of the caverns beneath Castrum Occidens without incident. Seeing as you were handpicked by Lady Alisaie herself, your success came as no surprise, but that doesn't make it any less impressive.
The investigation continues in other locales, to be sure, but I am reassured in the knowledge that my lady is in good hands.
Honored ally, what brings you to the Ring of Ash?

Should you bear wounds from the field of battle, then rest awhile and regain your strength. A warrior must stand proud and tall that <If(PlayerParameter(4))>she<Else/>he</If> might always stare death in the eye.
Chosen One is but little one, yet knows more of the forest and its secrets than this one. This one is not worthy...
<split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>! This one cannot thank you enough for─
...Ah, do forgive me. With all my time in Little Solace, this one─er, I seem to have picked up a few of our friends' quirks and mannerisms.
Oh, don't look at me like that, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>! I can assure you I have no designs on your undergarments. Now where did I put my journal...?
Have you noticed, overdweller? Changes have come to the 789th Order Dig─transformations, alterations, changes!
Yes, yes, many changes at the dig. Firstly, nap time has been cut from four hours to three. Secondly, all pickmen must at least think about picking up their pickaxe once a day.
Thirdly... \\<yawn> Ah, but Gi Gu must see to important business. Overdweller will return in three hours, yes?
Ye'll not believe this, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>, but I saw Gi Gu lift his pickaxe for the first time in nearly a fortnight.
Promptly fell on 'is arse and dozed off before comin' within ten yalms of the mines, 'course. Still, progress is progress.

Pshhh... <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>, you are welcome in the nursssery. Ssstay, tell tall tales to the ssspawnlings, and partake of our bounty. There is always more fishhh broth for our shhhorewalker clutchmate!
Rumors are rife of late about an adventurer who set foot within that haunted manor and emerged to tell the tale.
I recall the name <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,2)> being bandied about. Does that ring a bell with you, friend?
Rumor has it a party of adventurers quelled the latest uprising by the hecatoncheires.
Though, if the Stone Torches are to be believed, there never was another uprising.
Arlh told you about that, did he? Bah, some people don't know when to keep their mouths shut.
I'd be lying if I said I wasn't interested in paying a visit to Halatali myself. But for now, I'm content to drink and listen to the stories of others.
Whatever company we kept then, we're cooks now and proud of it. Aye, no snow-lined ways for us!
A shame he has to spend his days feeding wealthy ingrates, whereas I get to feed honest folk.

Well, well! If it ain't wossname, the hardy lasslad what stood by me side when I single-handedly─well, guess it wasn't quite singlehandedly if ye were there, but who gives a wotsit?─drove that sea-spawned songstress back to the depths.

Eh? Wasn't quite how it happened, ye say? That may well be, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>missy<Else/>sonny</If>, but when ye get to be ol' Mimidoa's age, such details are quick to slip from yer noggin─'specially when there's nails what need hammerin' and winsome lasses what need carousin'. Never too old for a spot o' carousin'.
'Nother 'nitiate, eh? Well, grab yerself a hammer an' some nails. With that hells-born harlot out of our hair, it's time we got down to the things what matter.

Eh? Things like what, ye say? Fer 'nitiates like you, things like hammerin'. Fer me, things like watchin' you hammer, for one, an' carousin' with rosy-cheeked lasses. As a wise man─bugger me if I can remember 'is name─once said, ain't never too old for a spot o' carousin'.
I cannot thank you enough, friend. With the siren silenced, the restoration effort has begun in earnest─and my lifelong dream of working under Master Mimidoa is realized at last.
He's a hard taskmaster, and his eye's wont to wander from time to time, but still, there's no place that I'd rather be.
Upon my father's and brother's graves, I swear─Pharos Sirius will again burn bright, and these hands will see it done.
Welcome to the Drowning Wench, a place to leave your cares and troubles behind.
I'll say that again: your cares and your troubles. You'll be taking the contents of your innards with you, or you'll not find the Wench so welcoming on your next visit.

We've recently procured a shipment o' sands an' oil o' time. Ain't nothin' more effective for restorin' old arms an' armor to mint condition, I tell you. If you're interested, I can fix you with some in exchange for mark logs.

These logs are kept by them as chase after elite marks in the Hunt, the bounty system what the Eorzean Alliance set up. In their lust for riches an' glory, hunters often end up dead, leavin' behind their worldly possessions.

Why do we want these, you ask? Let's just say there's a small but dedicated group o' people who derive pleasure from gettin' a peek at the lives o' the dearly departed. There's good coin to be made in satisfyin' their morbid taste.
I'm sorry, but can it wait? I'm rather busy right now with one of Rowena's thankless tasks.
The past belongs in the past, so they say. But there're things in life that refuse to stay there, no matter how much you will it. \\<sigh>
You're the adventurer what goes around slayin' gods, right? Then you ought to be familiar with those arms what're blessed by primals. Aye, them showy things what look like the beings.

But did you know that some o' these arms can be made mightier? Take those as harbor the power o' Shiva, for instance─the true Ice somethin's. These can be made mightier if you've got a pinch o' this stuff called diamond dust.
If you happen to have a true Ice weapon and some diamond dust, bring 'em to me and I'll see the former enhanced.

I welcome you, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)> of the black. It was only with your aid that I did unearth the answers sought by my ancestors, and for this I thank you. And yet each answer is but a stepping-stone to yet another question...

Tireless effort, unwavering focus. Harmony and unity of purpose, unobstructed by differences of tribe or nation. This is the goal I would strive for with the rest of my days─a goal that I am proud to share with you, friend.
If we fail at this mission, Gridania's relations with the sylphs could be damaged beyond repair. We must succeed at all costs!
I do not regret turning away the petitioners. They must understand the reality of their situation. The refugee issue will not be solved by the Scions alone.
That said, I am not without sympathy for their plight. I would do what I can to bring them some measure of succor. We are counting on your efforts, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>.
We will entrust the Lord of Levin to you. I have discussed the matter with Urianger as well. He may be able to offer some measure of assistance.
While the greatest challenges still lie ahead, we have earned a measure of peace for the moment.

If you are looking to pass the time before your next mission, I suggest you walk the streets and turn an ear to those around you. Revenant's Toll abounds with colorful characters these days. You are like to find their stories entertaining and enlightening both.
With the primal threat presently subdued, now is the perfect time to focus on new endeavors.
Alphinaud has long been laying the groundwork for this organization of his, and he looks to you to help turn his proposal into reality. Pray lend him what aid you can.
With the formation of the Crystal Braves, the Scions have gained a powerful ally, but with great power comes greater responsibility.
We must ever remain focused on our ultimate goal, that we can use our newfound power wisely.
Never is a woman more lovely than when she's hard at work, I say. A wild rose, strong and beautiful, blooming tall in the face of the frozen winds...
I told F'lhaminn all about our adventures in the Sylphlands, fake Thancred and all. Er, you won't tell the real Thancred, will you?
With the Doman younglings dashing around hither and yon, there's hardly a moment of peace to be had.
That said, traveling with Yda, it's not as if I knew much peace to begin with...
The storm has passed and a moment's quietude is ours. Tataru is using her newfound time to further her studies, and I would follow her example.
If living in Eorzea has taught us anything at all, it's that such restful moments are fleeting. Dark clouds ever stir anew on the horizon.
I do not know where we would be without Higiri─the girl has worked tirelessly for us every day since her arrival. Do you suppose all Doman women are so diligent?
Repetition and routine beget skill. Skill begets confidence. I would do what I can to see the Domans regain their strength of will.
Ah, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. Care to watch the lessons before you journey on your way? I daresay your presence would go far to inspire the younglings.
Many of my countrymen have found work as frontier hands, helping to transport supplies and continue the expansion of Revenant's Toll.
I have been tasked with keeping the equipment here in good repair. It is not particularly glamorous work, but I would help in whatever way I can.
Despite all the hardships they have faced, the younglings pursue their training with great zeal. We older ones would do well to follow their example.
One hundred thirty-seven, one hundred thirty-eight, one hundred thirty─oh, hello there!
I've been charged with keeping inventory. F'lhaminn tells me it's a vitally important─ Oh dear! I seem to have lost count.
Our lessons are through for the moment, but a true adventurer never shirks his duties. I say we shall go on a patrol of Revenant's Toll!
Are you taking a rest, too? Promise you'll play with us again soon. That game of hide-and-seek in Vesper Bay was the most fun I've had in forever!
Yozan's always been the strongest of us, but even he's no match for Koharu when she's mad.
If I were as big as a mountain and strong as a bear like Mister Boulder is, maybe I would like fighting more...
I daresay they heard you talking a malm away. Yda and Thancred dashed out not moments ago. Will they ever start acting their age?
Just as some children possess wisdom beyond their years, some adults are little more than children writ large.
Remember this, and it should save you a measure of frustration in your dealings with those around you.
Nothing warms me inside quite like Higiri's tea. Truly, it is salve for the body and soul.
Higiri has told me about a Doman tea with a most remarkable fragrance. What I would not give to taste it for myself!
Where did everyone run off to all of a sudden? It is not that I mind so much─the quiet is most conducive to focusing on my tasks.

So turn we to heroes, of conscience unstained.♪
May all stop at naught till what's lost is regained.♪
Oh, hello again. F'lhaminn has been teaching me some Eorzean ballads. Though I hail from a faraway land, there is something about music that truly transcends borders.
You've done well, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. Why don't you join me at the counter for a drink? My treat.
Might I suggest those seats over there by F'lhaminn and Higiri? Though, of course, anywhere would suffice!
I-I'm not sleeping! I was just engrossed in thought, th-that's all!
As is oft said, trouble arrives when you least expect it. It is precisely when things appear to be proceeding according to plan that we must needs steel ourselves for impending danger.
...Ahem! Are you listening, Yda!?
Enjoy your respite, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>, for you certainly have earned it. Just do not relax your guard overmuch─unlike a certain someone here.
With everyone coming back, it's gotten quite lively around here of late. Why, at times it almost reminds me of the old days at the Waking Sands.
Not only are Higiri's culinary creations positively delicious, you should see her at work in the kitchen! She wields a knife like nothing I've ever seen!
I spend the better part of my days crossing blades with children, but I approach these lessons with as much fire as any battle I've ever fought.
The Domans may have found refuge here, but none are so naive as to think their troubles are over. I would prepare them in body and spirit for the challenges that yet lie ahead.
Hoary Boulder's sparring practice grows more spirited by the day. I hope only that it is not too spirited for the younglings who face him.

Some might think the life of an adventurer a carefree one, but you and I know that this is far from the truth. While you may not be beholden to a single lord, you bear the weight of an entire realm's expectations on your shoulders.
Doma is lost, but if we keep our heads high and learn from our experiences in this place, perhaps aught may yet be done for our homeland.
Sadly, I lack the ingredients and seasonings needed to truly recreate the taste of my homeland. That said, I've come to enjoy this challenge to my culinary skills.
Mister Boulder is a demanding teacher, but we trained hard in Doma too! We'll not bend so easily!
Just you watch! Someday I'll be as strong as you, and I'll protect everyone from the Garleans!
Look at Mister Boulder, with his shining armor and his giant sword. Do you think I'll ever be strong enough to wield a blade like that?
Mister Boulder says we must be brave, but that's easy for him to say. He's big and strong, but I'm small and weak.
Take care, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>! I look forward to hearing all about your adventures when you return!
Duty calls? Well, no matter the task, I have faith you will see it through to the end.
Worried about leaving us alone? Don't be. While the Archons are away, Hoary Boulder will keep the little ones safe!
Mayhap one day we shall accompany you into the field. But for now, we must see to less glamorous duties.
The children are quick to take to Eorzean ways, but I cannot claim the same...flexibility.
Speaking with Master Coultenet has opened my eyes to a great many things. I had no idea the world outside Doma was so strange and wonderful!
I tried substituting native ingredients several times, but the result was but a pale imitation of authentic Doman cuisine...
<If(PlayerParameter(4))>Miss<Else/>Mister</If> <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>! Is it true you're going to go adventuring again? I'm so jealous!
Hey, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>Miss<Else/>Mister</If> <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>, what's a “Ramuh”? Is it cute and fluffy like a horsebird?
After we parted in Ul'dah, I paid a visit to the refugees. Though a fundamental solution remains far off, I believe that at the very least there should be no armed uprisings in the near future.
I am given to understand that you resolved the matter of Ramuh. I will ask Minfilia for a full report when next we speak. You have done well, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>.
My grandfather formed the Circle of Knowing in the hopes that, through the accumulation of knowledge, Eorzea might be saved from disaster foretold.
A band of champions brought together by a common goal, to lead our realm to a better tomorrow. Though our means may differ, I would like to believe I do him proud in undertaking this new endeavor.
Your bout with Hoary Boulder was more stirring than a hundred lines of my most passionate poetry. Mayhaps I should arrange a sparring match of my own...
I can't wait for Alphinaud to start his new company. I love making new friends!
I wish Yda were not so eager to look to the future when we have so many problems in the here and now...
I fear Yda's boundless optimism is beginning to affect my better judgment. And your tendency to triumph against the most terrible of foes is certainly not helping matters.
No, this won't do at all! And then I'll have to─ Oh, hello, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>! If you don't mind, I'm terribly busy at the moment!
'Tis not enough that I am here for my daughter─I must do what little I can to help you all succeed in your monumental tasks.
<split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>! I must thank you again for agreeing to our bout.
...And I must thank the gods 'twas not a duel to the death! I will, however, cherish the lesson of each scrape and bruise as I work to better my swordplay.
I thought the idea foolish at first, but it seems that sparring match well served its purpose. Why, I can hardly wait to return to my studies and seek to improve upon my technique!

My people's spirits were thoroughly crushed by the loss of our homeland, but thanks to your courage and generosity I see their inner flames once more flicker back to life. I, too, have felt my strength of will make a gradual return.
Our Doman farming methods have been adopted here on the frontier. 'Tis too early yet to know if they will prove to be effective...
This place has become as a hive, and its bees flit about in constant motion. Perhaps a soothing pot of tea will coax one or two to alight and take a moment's rest.
Mister Boulder fought well, but he was no match for you, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>Miss<Else/>Mister</If> <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>!
Just you wait! One day I'll be good enough to knock you from the top of your mountain!
Mister Boulder is sore and beaten, but he said he'd return straight to his training. Heh heh, I don't think he likes to lose!
We need to decide who in our Adventurers' Guild will do what. I'm fairly sure Yozan will have to be the swordfighter─he always has to be in the thick of the action.
I like the way Mister Coultenet fought─no swords or fists. I wonder, if I studied hard, would I be able to cast spells like that too?
Ever since Higiri started preparing our meals, I swear I've never felt better.
They say Doman cuisine is highly nourishing, but I'd sooner attribute it to the loving care she puts into her culinary creations.
They say the fastest way to a man's heart is through his stomach, and I'm not wont to disagree.
Papalymo refuses to spar with me. He says he has more important matters to attend to, but I think he's just afraid to lose!

Sparring bouts to raise awareness of the Crystal Braves? Intriguing, though I cannot help but feel there are more pressing tasks at hand. Perhaps Tataru requires aid in compiling the company roster...

Every time I speak to Riol, I realize how much there is that I do not yet understand about the kobolds. I am fortunate indeed to count a former member of the Company of Heroes as friend and confidant.
The Crystal Braves... 'Tis a most fitting name for a company of champions summoned together by the Mothercrystal, would you not agree?
The blue of the uniform represents the Crystal's Light─pure and unadulterated, a beacon of hope. The crystal sword is the sign of those who would stand strong in the face of danger.
Until the day that my Crystal Braves are a guiding light for all of Eorzea, I will not give up the fight.
Ohgodsohgods! I thought I was finished with the roster, but I missed a name and had to start all over. As if I didn't have enough work to do already!
Anyone with a pair of eyes can see that Thancred is thoroughly besmitten with Higiri. Then again, subtlety has never been one of his strengths...
Urianger has asked me to watch over the Doman women, that they do not come to any more suffering than they have already endured...
'Tis always inspiring to speak with a person of vision. If there is aught I might do to be of service to this new company, you know where to find me.
Come to mention it, the younglings seem to have run off somewhere. I do hope they're not up to any mischief...
I hear a new company has been formed. I would be of service in whatever humble way I can.
I am studying Eorzean military drills, in the hope that I might better understand this new organization.
Mister Thancred has taken quite a fancy to Doman cuisine. Several times a day he tells me that one of my dishes is the best he's ever tasted.
His praise is most heartening, though I cannot help but feel he has a wont for exaggeration...
The Crystal Braves! Why, just saying the name makes me feel strong!

I've been thinking of changing the name of our guild to “The Doman Braves.” How does that sound to you, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>Miss<Else/>Mister</If> <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>?
We hereby name Yozan commander of the Doman Braves!
For the freedom of all! For the freedom of all! For the freedom of all!
It just doesn't sound the same when I say it...
Our Doman Adventurers' Guild could use a new name. Say, do you have any ideas?
Seein' this lass sure brings back memories. I was jus' sharin' a couple o' juicy secrets with her.
You've brought in quite a few new recruits, haven't you? Your reputation extends far beyond Little Ala Mhigo, it would seem, and deservedly so.
Why, meeting you has given me something to strive for. Remember the name of Wilred! I shall hone both body and mind and do you and my fellow Braves proud.
This uniform rather suits me, would you not say? Or perhaps it is I that suits it.
After all my transgressions, I am grateful indeed for this chance to start anew. Buscarron! Laurentius shall do you proud!
Alphinaud's words were most heart-stirring, would you not agree? Truth be told, I worry what I can offer to such a lofty organization, but I will do all in my power to make my fellow Braves proud!
The formation of the Crystal Braves has lifted everyone's spirits. My hopes are as high as the next man, but we'll not know what this company is truly made of till we face our first mission.
We've started dealing in Ironworks gear. As the name suggests, these items are made by Garlond Ironworks, and the quality is exceptional. And as you'd expect, you won't find them anywhere else.
Picking up the scent of profit, Rowena quickly secured an exclusive deal to be the realm's sole supplier. The woman's purse continues to grow fat with coin, but we hirelings see nary a gil of it.
Dreams are well and good, but if you live with your head in the clouds, sooner or later you'll find yourself on your rear. My sorry, drink-sodden son is an example of this.
The Stone Vigil returns to Ishgard! Hail, <String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, and bless you for the work you've done today.
We'll have the perimeter sealed up, then make the place fit to garrison again. It'll be the jewel of our defenses, you'll see!
I had plans for piercing the defenses, but fie! The Vigil was retaken ere I could bend my commander's ear. I must see to restoring the keep, the Fury save me.
It's House Durendaire that sees to Whitebrim Front, and a good thing too. Only the four High Houses have the coin and men to rebuild the Stone Vigil, and none're flusher than Durendaire.
'Twas well you came, else we would not have won this day. Only a knight errant may break a stalemate, my lady mother used to say.
Your deeds are known to all at the Front─but false would I speak if I said you were accepted by all. Pride hardens resolve and hearts alike.
Ishgard was all I knew until I was almost a woman grown. 'Twas to be a brief spell, my time on the road─but now I find myself mulling an adventurer's life.
News from Coerthas talks of naught but the part you played in the retaking of the Stone Vigil. I read you correctly, did I not? A <If(PlayerParameter(4))>woman<Else/>man</If> of rare quality.
If you see Spenser around, tell him to get his sorry arse back in here. Bastard stumbled out without paying his tab...again.
Master Bugaal Ja's passion for both bathing and dancing is truly unparalleled. I am sure it is but a matter of time before his art finds a receptive audience.
Havin' been founded by pirates, Limsa's long been the hub for piracy. But those days're comin' to an end, mark me words, an' it's all for the greater good.
...Eh? Who's the last Mistbeard, ye ask? Seven hells, yer a right daft sod, ain't ye? Me an' the chief was as subtle 'bout it as a bleedin' sledgehammer!
Gridania─lovely, dark, and deep. These woods are ours to guard, secure between the coils of honor and duty...
Vannes is me own flesh and blood, heir to the Brugaire Consortium. It barely needs sayin' that 'e'd settle for no less than the most storied beauty the realm over.
I am Vannes, heir to the chairmanship of the Brugaire Consortium. And who exactly were you, again?
...I'm sorry. I just realized that I don't particularly care.
All I have done to raise Arabella to a beautiful young woman has been in anticipation of this day. I have never been more proud to call myself her father.
Good food, good drink, an' good tidin's. That today's announcement will send even more gil flowin' into our coffers only makes the wine taste all the sweeter.
Oh, how I am looking forward to meeting Miss Arabella. They say many a song is sung of her beauty.
Mind you, there was a song or two sung of me in my day.

Renting out Master Gegeruju's private property would be almost unthinkable for most folk. But gil talks, and neither the Brugaire Consortium nor the East Aldenard Trading Company are in any danger of running their coffers dry.
The phantom thief may have eluded us again, but his dramatic appearance at the banquet made for quite the story in itself.
“I shall come to claim the victor's spoils,” the card said. I plan to head straight to the Coliseum to investigate.

The flame is not the fuel, praise the Traders. The Immortal Flames depend not on any one soldier─not even Raubahn Aldynn. Low it may burn at times, but as long as there are men willing to serve, it is forever.
The poets can romanticize it all they want, but a life without coin is no life at all.

Vintage equipment's fallen out of favor of late. Though we still deal in them, at Rowena's behest, they're now bespoke items. She won't have valuable shelf space being taken up by wares that don't sell, you see.
Sorry, but I've my hands full assisting Eginolf with his orders. You're free to stand there and gape at the shelves all you wish, but if you need aught else, I'm afraid I cannot be of any assistance.
Titan's Bane! Master Gegeruju told me that this feast would draw esteemed personages from across the realm, but I was not expecting to see you among them.
Felling primals, solving mysteries─you certainly know how to keep yourself busy.
They tell me this Arabella is quite the beauty. Do you suppose she'd be interested in earning a bit of extra coin as one of my dancers?
You have recorded twenty vistas to your sightseeing log. Report to Millith Ironheart at Apkallu Falls in Gridania.
Is there aught I may do to serve you? I stand ever at the ready. For the freedom of all!
For the freedom of all! For the freedom of all! For the freedom of all!
The first few times I said it, I must confess to feeling some embarrassment, but it's starting to grow on me.
The greater our successes, the more our name will grow. The more our name grows, the greater the profits to be had. I can scarcely contain my anticipation for our first mission.
Any friend of Eginolf is more than welcome here. How might I help you?
Lord Ramuh judged walking one worthy? This one is duly impressed! Lord Ramuh turns most walking ones into toasty ones.

Being born with one red eye, I did not have the most pleasant of childhoods. You know what they say: children can be cruel. The end result being that I grew up determined to uncover the truth of the trait.
Much and more yet remains beyond my knowing, but one thing is certain: the nearer I draw to the heart of the Crystal Tower, the more I am convinced that an important memory eludes me.
Even without Dalamud in the heavens, the Crystal Tower is capable of generating vast amounts of energy. It's only a matter of time before the voidgate is thrown open fully.

Knowing this, Nero used us in order to secure safe passage to the tower's apex. Though I doubt that any of us fell for his ruse, we let the scoundrel do as he pleased nonetheless. Deep down, we all want to believe that a man can change for the better...
Voidgates and the like are a thaumaturge's domain. Engineers like me and Wedge are out of our depth.
Having said that, we're not entirely useless here. The workings of the Crystal Tower itself are a language we understand. If there's something to decipher, we mean to decipher it.
This is just my humble opinion, but a man like Emperor Xande wouldn't leave anything to chance. Before we arrived at the tower's apex, he would've completed his preparations to open the voidgate.
That's why the gate manifested so soon after you defeated him, and poor Unei and Doga were sucked in. Thoroughness and the lust for nihility make for a dreadful combination...

Ah, <If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(52),0))><split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)><Else/><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(53),0))><Head><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(52),0))><sheet(GCRankLimsaMaleText,PlayerParameter(52),8)><Else/> </If><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(53),0))><sheet(GCRankGridaniaMaleText,PlayerParameter(53),8)><Else/> </If><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(54),0))><sheet(GCRankUldahMaleText,PlayerParameter(54),8)><Else/> </If></Head> <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,2)><Else/><split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)></If></If>. I hear that you have quieted Ramuh's thunder once more. It is clear we entrusted the task to the right <If(PlayerParameter(4))>woman<Else/>man</If>.

As you know well by now, the sylphs are not as simple a people as they might seem to an outsider. In many ways, the complexity of the relationships between the various factions of their society rivals that of our own.
This is the venue for the, um, cannon event for the Moonfire Faire. It's fun, it packs a punch, and─most important of all─it's family friendly!

I'm the chairman...or chief chaperone...or something of the Moonfire Faire. Sounds fancy, I know, but at the end of the day, I'm just another soul working to make the faire a rousing success. We're all in this together!
The Moonfire Faire's in full swing in Limsa Lominsa, and we're recruiting adventurers to help out with this year's festivities. Do tell all your friends!
The Adventurers' Guild is currently hosting the Moonfire Faire in Limsa Lominsa, and we're recruiting people to help make this year's festivities the merriest ever. Please spread the word!
Moon–fire Fa–ire!♪ In Lim–sa Lo–minsa!♪ Hah hah hah! Come join us for the Moonfire Faire, brought to you by the Adventurers' Guild!
Beating the heat─that's what any summer festival worth its salt offers participants, and the Moonfire Faire is no slouch. Here at the Rousing Douse event, refreshingly cool is the order of business!
No Moonfire Faire can be considered complete without dazzling fireworks. Here at the Very Cherry Bomb event, we set off lots and lots of them!
You've served this nation well. I've no doubt that even greater adventures lie in your future. Go forth and do Limsa proud!
Ah, what I wouldn't give to get out and see the realm from time to time. Do you reckon those moogles are still looking for help?
I wish I could promise you that my brother will learn from his experience, but he has proven to have a rather short memory in the past...
Spenser has not been around of late. Do you suppose he has freed himself from his demons at last?
How fares your chocobo? Should you discover anything noteworthy as you raise your bird, I would be most grateful if you could share your observations.
The chocobos are as varied as you and I in what they favor, aye. Grow a sundry of greens and you'll see that's so.

It would seem some entrepreneurs decided to take advantage of your hard work. They've set about renovating the facilities so that Halatali might once more serve as training grounds for Coliseum gladiators.

Full glad I was to be rid of the wild beasts, but now the new owners have brought even more bloodthirsty creatures─and men! I say, who is going to take responsibility when this spirals out of control!?
Hey, I know you! What with you followin' that half-crazed inspector hither and yon on his madcap cases, I reckon you've worked up quite a thirst. I've got a fine vintage I reckon you might fancy.

Thanks to you, this Moonfire Faire's been a rousing success. That said, the festivities still continue, so don't be slacking off just yet, eh? Keep having a good time, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>, and see that others do the same!
I understand the appeal, I do. But a man can do more good living humbly for a cause than dying nobly for one.
That was some nasty work in the caves. Good that you did it, though. Wouldn't want our friends to get even more carried away.
People ought to be more grateful for what they've got, don't you think?
I wasn't there, and I won't presume to pass judgment, but... They will remember what you did─and so should you.

Once again, allow me to express my thanks, <If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(54),0))><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(54),127))><Head><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(52),0))><sheet(GCRankLimsaMaleText,PlayerParameter(52),8)><Else/> </If><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(53),0))><sheet(GCRankGridaniaMaleText,PlayerParameter(53),8)><Else/> </If><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(54),0))><sheet(GCRankUldahMaleText,PlayerParameter(54),8)><Else/> </If></Head> <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,2)><Else/><split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)></If><Else/><split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)></If>. Were it not for your efforts, the violence might have continued unabated for some time.
The situation is far from resolved, but I have faith that one day these events will be but a distant memory.
We all have it coming, soldier. Don't think that you're an exception.
Beg your pardon, Scion, but I cannot permit you to enter the Fragrant Chamber at this time. Pray step away from the doors.
This one heard! This one felt! Walking one has been judged worthy by Lord Ramuh.
Elder one is most grateful to walking one. These ones' crystal has found a good home with walking one.
To think that I'd see the day when Revenant's Toll became a bustling hub for adventurers. Almost warrants giving the place a new name, wouldn't you say?
That said, the influx of visitors doesn't come without problems─for Tataru most of all, and those of us who have to give an ear to her griping.
What manner of supplies did the heretics abscond with, you ask? Worry yourself not─'twas naught that cannot be replaced.
Save for one item to which I personally had taken a fancy. Are you perchance familiar with the dress of the Cascadiers?
Needless to say, frippery so...revealing...is not so easily had in these parts. 'Tis a shame to see it lost.

So Landenel has finally come to understand the commander's wish. That is well. With this realization, he may begin walking his own path and fulfill his true potential. Thank you for standing by him throughout his inner struggle.
Are you looking for something special today? Whether you seek a tasteful tribute to those lost in the Calamity or a symbol of our realm's rebirth, you're sure to find what you need!
Just think how much more poignant those fireworks would be with something to remember them by. Blue comets are fleeting but a souvenir─a souvenir is forever!
You seem fascinated by my raiments. I am flattered! My betrothed made them─as dextrous with a needle as she is with a sword, that one! A bit short-tempered, but we all have our faults, don't we?
Look at that, fireworks. Just had 'em for the Moonfire Faire, didn't we? This lot's for the Calamity, though.
Look at 'em colors! Musta been a deal of work for the pyromancers. That's what I call a tribute, aye.
Funny thing, grief. You're a bow drawn, don't even know the strain till somethin' releases it─somethin' like these fireworks.
Bawled like a baby the first night the Adventurers' Guild put on the display, I did. They say there's one in every city. A footloose <If(PlayerParameter(4))>lass<Else/>lad</If> could see 'em all...
You see those fireworks? A tribute to the dead, they say, but not I─no. What do we know of the dead and their ways? They have their new duties in the halls of the Twelve.
Those night-blooms are for us, for the living. Shall we scan the sky anxious as smallholders, cringing at every strange light? Or shall we remember what it was to stand tall and breathe deep?
Seen the remembrance fireworks for the Calamity, have you? And here I was thinking 'twas more o' the Moonfire Faire!
I look up and say a prayer for every burst. And then I'm at peace awhile. That there's the difference 'tween memory and remembrance...
More fireworks at night, have you marked them? They say it's for the dead, that it's in remembrance of the Calamity.
What I want is to forget, not remember. Am I to ooh and aah over fire in the sky? A rain of fire there was, and my brother, he...no, they are not for me, these fireworks.

Oh no, these are not for the Moonfire Faire. These fireworks are in remembrance of the Calamity─and rebirth of the realm. It's the Adventurers' Guild that paints the night sky thus. Have you heard them singing?

Have light, will travel, if your nights be dark～♪
An adventure's naught if not done on a lark...♪
A hardy lot, and merry too!
Cast out, I once was, but by Chief Totoloc, I was saved! To repay this kindness, most able of Ehcatl, I shall become. My words, mark them well! Squahaha!
“Garuda! Garuda!” Ever cry out for the goddess, buzzards do. Yet care one whit for buzzards, Garuda does not. What use have Ehcatl for goddess like that!?
Sqwak sqwak! Knotcounter of Ehcatl, this one is. Sqwak! Money, time is, and time for chatter, this one has not. Sqwak!
Squawk! Disturb me, featherless one must not! Hard at work on revolutionary new control mechanism, I am! Go here, this does, and...squawk! Perfection!
Crafter, featherless one is? Caw! Good things, I hear, of featherless ones' crafting, but perfection, I demand. Pass my inspections, you shall, or peck out your eyes, I will. Caw!
Sqqquawk! Get underfoot, featherless one must not! Hard at work, engineers are! No rest for the Ehcatl Nine till Ayatlan, we reclaim!

Welcome to the Coerthas branch office of Highwind Skyways! ...Sounds all grand and official when you say it like that, but in truth, it's just poor little Templeton─banished to this godsforsaken waste because he rubbed a few of his superiors the wrong way.
That said, being able to operate without constant supervision does afford certain...opportunities. Opportunities that might be mutually beneficial to those to whom I take a liking. \\<wink> \\<wink>

Hello there, adventurer! This crafting facility is for the use of artisans with “special” tasks. If you don't have any special tasks, then I must ask you to step aside and let someone else take their turn.
Greetings! The crafting facility here at Treespeak Stables is primarily for the purpose of forging tools for the stablehands, but our doors─assuming we had any─are open to all!
Welcome to the Diamond Forge. Here we have but one goal: to offer the services of our crafting facilities in accordance with the wishes of the Revenant's Toll chapter of the Adventurers' Guild.
If it's Rowena you seek, you'll find her out the door and to your right. If there is naught else we can help you with, however, then I must ask you to leave.
In a place like Camp Dragonhead, there is no shortage of crafters eager to utilize our facilities. Some items are best forged in the cold, after all.
Is it not wonderful that our benefactors are generous enough to grant access to all? Truly, there is naught more rewarding than aiding crafters with their artistic pursuits!
Business is positively booming of late─thanks in no small part to you, friend!
...But while we'd like nothing more than to serve you a grand feast to repay you for your efforts, I'm afraid we're booked up for three moons hence. Ever so sorry about that.
To fly higher than any other is Ehcatl Nine's dream. But before we can fly, make wings, we must! Squawk!
Supplies, I gather, swiftly and in bulk. Consumed, they are, and swifter still. Thankless work, this is. Squawk!
The more I learn of it, the more I come to understand what a remarkable airship the Dezul Qualan truly is! To be able to work on such a vessel─why, it is an engineer's dream come true!
My wares, I will trade, to friends of Ehcatl. Get nothing from me, featherless neukers will. Nothing but squawk. Squawwwk!
Skaetswys and I 'ave been together since our piratin' days. Always 'ad a knack for gettin' 'erself into trouble.
...An' gettin' others out of it, which is why we could never stay angry at 'er for too long.

Well, if it isn't <If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(52),0))><Head><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(52),0))><sheet(GCRankLimsaMaleText,PlayerParameter(52),8)><Else/> </If><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(53),0))><sheet(GCRankGridaniaMaleText,PlayerParameter(53),8)><Else/> </If><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(54),0))><sheet(GCRankUldahMaleText,PlayerParameter(54),8)><Else/> </If></Head> <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,2)><Else/><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(53),0))><split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)><Else/><split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)></If></If>, the <If(PlayerParameter(4))>woman<Else/>man</If> who solved the matter o' the missin' beastmen. Ye just keep findin' ways to outdo yerself, don't ye?

I am not privy as to the particulars, but I am told that we have quite a crisis on our hands. Go safely, <If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(52),0))><split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)><Else/><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(53),0))><Head><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(52),0))><sheet(GCRankLimsaMaleText,PlayerParameter(52),8)><Else/> </If><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(53),0))><sheet(GCRankGridaniaMaleText,PlayerParameter(53),8)><Else/> </If><If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(54),0))><sheet(GCRankUldahMaleText,PlayerParameter(54),8)><Else/> </If></Head> <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,2)><Else/><split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)></If></If>, and may the elementals watch over you.

In resolving the matter of the missing beastmen and bringing Memeriga to justice, you have truly gone above and beyond the call of duty.

Our greatest victories are in the battles we need never fight. In working to build a lasting peace with the beastmen, you have prevented needless bloodshed and loss.
